# Scoreboard — Project Architecture

## Purpose

Beach tennis scoreboard application. Tracks points, games, sets and matches in real time following official beach tennis rules.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | React 19 |
| Language | TypeScript 5.9 |
| Build | Vite 8 |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS 4 (`@tailwindcss/vite` plugin) |
| Routing | TanStack Router (code-based, `apps/frontend/src/router.tsx`) |
| Testing | Vitest 4 |
| Package manager | pnpm workspaces |
| Monorepo | Turborepo |
| CI/CD | GitHub Actions + release-it + Conventional Commits |

## Monorepo Structure

```
scoreboard/                     ← workspace root
├── apps/
│   └── frontend/               ← Vite app (React + UI)
├── packages/
│   ├── core/                   ← @scoreboard/core — DDD domain + application layer
│   └── shared/                 ← shared code (future)
├── turbo.json                  ← Turborepo task pipeline
└── pnpm-workspace.yaml         ← pnpm workspace declaration
```

Turborepo tasks (run from root): `dev`, `build`, `check-types`, `lint`, `test`.
The `build` and `check-types` scripts are **separate** so Turborepo can run them in parallel.

## Package: `@scoreboard/core` (`packages/core`)

Pure TypeScript — no React, no Vite, no Tailwind. Framework-agnostic domain and application layer.

```
packages/core/src/
├── domain/               ← Domain layer (pure, no framework dependencies)
│   ├── shared/           ← Base classes and shared types
│   ├── value-objects/    ← Immutable VOs (Team, MatchConfig)
│   ├── events/           ← Domain events (PointScored, GameWon, SetWon, MatchWon)
│   ├── point.entity.ts
│   ├── game.entity.ts
│   ├── set.entity.ts
│   └── match.aggregate.ts  ← Aggregate root
├── application/          ← Use cases (CQRS)
│   ├── shared/           ← ICommandHandler, IQueryHandler, MatchDto
│   ├── commands/         ← CreateMatch, StartMatch, ScorePoint
│   └── queries/          ← GetMatch → MatchDto
└── infrastructure/
    └── database/         ← Repository interfaces (ports)
        ├── match-repository.interface.ts
        └── player-repository.interface.ts
```

## App: `apps/frontend`

```
apps/frontend/src/
├── infrastructure/       ← Concrete adapters (RxDB + IndexedDB)
│   └── persistence/
│       ├── database.ts
│       ├── match.schema.ts
│       ├── match.serializer.ts
│       ├── rxdb-match.repository.ts
│       └── rxdb-player.repository.ts
├── hooks/                ← React custom hooks (bridge application → UI)
├── pages/                ← Route-level components (Login, Scoreboard, Players)
└── router.tsx            ← TanStack Router route tree
```

Imports from `@scoreboard/core` use the package alias (e.g. `import { Match } from '@scoreboard/core/domain/match.aggregate'`).

## CI/CD

GitHub Actions + release-it + Conventional Commits. Full details in `cicd.mdc`.

- `ci.yml` — commitlint + check-types + test + build (triggers on PRs)
- `release.yml` — CI + per-package release with path-based change detection (triggers on push to `main`)
- Commits follow `type(scope): description` — scopes: `core`, `frontend`, `shared`, `ci`, `deps`, `release`

## Key Architectural Decisions

1. **`@scoreboard/core` is framework-agnostic** — no React, no Vite, no Tailwind inside `packages/core/src/`.
2. **Aggregate root (`Match`) is the only public mutation surface** — call `match.start()` and `match.scorePoint()`. Never mutate inner entities directly.
3. **Domain events** are collected via `match.pullDomainEvents()` after each mutation and dispatched by the application layer.
4. **No parameter properties** in constructors — `erasableSyntaxOnly: true` in tsconfig. Use the Props pattern instead.
5. **Factory methods** (`Entity.create()`, `Entity.restore()`) replace `new Entity(...)` calls from outside the class.
6. **Tests live in `__tests__/`** folders at the same level as the file they test, inside `packages/core/src/`.
7. **Commits follow Conventional Commits** — use scoped commits (`feat(core):`, `fix(frontend):`) to trigger releases only for the affected package. See `cicd.mdc` for full details.
